name: Senator Jerry Moran
tweet_text: ✈Improving child safety on commercial airlines. Legislation I championed is included in #FAAReauthorization, directing the FAA to review and update the contents of emergency medical kids on planes – something that hasn’t been done in almost 20 years.

name: Senator Jerry Moran
tweet_text: ✈Highlighting the need for talented women in the aviation workforce and making certain the FAA facilitates their recruitment. Women comprise only 4% of flight engineers, 6% of pilots & 26% of air traffic controllers – a significant untapped pool of talent for the industry.

name: Senator Jerry Moran
tweet_text: ✈Preserving the Contract Weather Observers program. In recent years, the FAA has proposed eliminating the CWO program at airports such as @FlyICT. I’ve fought against elimination of the CWO program to preserve the highest levels of safety at airports.

name: Senator Jerry Moran
tweet_text: ✈Increasing fairness & reducing regulation for general aviation projects.

name: Senator Jerry Moran
tweet_text: ✈Reauthorizing the FAA’s Essential Air Service Program, which connects rural airports to the national system. Kansas airports currently participating in the EAS program include @GCKAirport, @FlyHays and @SalinaAirport. This bill reauthorizes the EAS program for five years.

name: Senator Jerry Moran
tweet_text: ✈The ability to build or replace contract towers and secure needed equipment to help enhance air traffic safety at Kansas airports, such as @FlyMHK and @HutchGov.

name: Senator Jerry Moran
tweet_text: ✈Strengthening the Federal Contract Tower Program. Kansas is home to eight contract air traffic control towers, which provide important safety services at small airports nationwide in a cost-effective manner – saving the FAA approximately $200 million annually.

name: Senator Jerry Moran
tweet_text: ✈Establishing fair treatment of UAS by tribal governments. The #FAAReauthorization Act amends the definition of “public aircraft” to include Unmanned Aircraft Systems that are owned and operated by a tribal government.

name: Senator Jerry Moran
tweet_text: ✈Acceleration of the safe integration of UAS technology. In May, @USDOT announced that @KDOTHQ was a winner of its UAS Integration Pilot Program. The IPP is a solid path forward to address airspace sovereignty & included in this bill is my language to codify & expand the IPP.

name: Senator Jerry Moran
tweet_text: ✈Reducing regulatory barriers for educational use of drones. Last Congress, I was the co-lead of legislation to reduce barriers for the use of small unmanned aerial systems at institutes of higher education.

name: Senator Jerry Moran
tweet_text: ✈Helping to close the skills gap in the aviation workforce. I am an original cosponsor of legislation, included in the FAA bill in its entirety, to create a pilot program within the FAA through which grants would be authorized to support technical and career education.

name: Senator Jerry Moran
tweet_text: ✈Supporting advanced materials research at @WichitaState that has played a critical role in the evolution and integration of aircraft materials and technologies by continuing the FAA Center of Excellence for Advanced Materials at WSU.

name: Senator Jerry Moran
tweet_text: ✈Bolstering aviation manufacturing by streamlining the aircraft certification process. These reforms will strengthen U.S. aviation sales and exports, help bring new safety technology to market and better utilize FAA and general aviation industry resources.

name: Senator Jerry Moran
tweet_text: Thank you for those who watched the #LandonLecture. As I stated in my remarks, I’m committed to making certain we #NeverForget 9/11 and how it refocused us as a nation on the things that bind us together rather than pull us apart. God Bless America today and everyday.

name: Senator Jerry Moran
tweet_text: May we #NeverForget September 11th, 2001. May we Never Forget the way we united in the aftermath of the attacks, as one nation under God. And may we renew our commitment to respecting one another, to working together for the common good and answering the call to serve.

name: Senator Jerry Moran
tweet_text: As I stood next to a New York City congressman from Brooklyn, we saw a nation under attack. While we disagree with each other more often than not, as we stood there, we saw each other as fathers, not foes; fellow Americans, not political enemies. #LandonLecture

name: Senator Jerry Moran
tweet_text: Her concern for me on that day and her efforts to make sure it was she who told our daughters their father was safe, rather than the television, is representative of a larger sacrifice that my family has made in order for me to continue to answer the calls of many. #LandonLecture

name: Senator Jerry Moran
tweet_text: One of the most important calls I took that day was from my wife, Robba. Before widely used cell phones, texting and email, she had no way to reach me besides calling my main office line.

name: Senator Jerry Moran
tweet_text: I felt the care and compassion of Kansans in ways that I had not before, and I am forever changed. #LandonLecture

name: Senator Jerry Moran
tweet_text: On this day, the most frightening day our nation has seen in this lifetime, Kansans chose to pick up the phone and offer their assistance, their thoughts and their prayers.

name: Senator Jerry Moran
tweet_text:
Earlier, I spoke about remaining in my office and answering Kansans’ telephone calls on September 11th.
